<subSubSection id="C33D6511FF86B14BFF53FAD9FDC719EF" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B98369AFF86B14BFF53FAD9FEC81A78" blockId="46.[227,348,1330,1356]" box="[227,348,1330,1356]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading id="D0D081F6FF86B14BFF53FAD9FEC81A78" bold="true" box="[227,348,1330,1356]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFF53FAD9FEC81A78" bold="true" box="[227,348,1330,1356]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369AFF86B14BFF53FA8AFDC719EF" blockId="46.[227,1437,1377,1755]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFF53FA8AFECC1A4F" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau" authorityYear="1835" box="[227,344,1377,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponerinae">Ponerinae</taxonomicName>
share the following characters: antennal toruli situated well-posterad anterior clypeal margin (except 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFEF5FA6FFE4F1AAA" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1974" box="[325,475,1412,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dolioponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFEF5FA6FFE4F1AAA" box="[325,475,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Dolioponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); at least 4 closed cells present on forewing (
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFBA8FA6FFB3A1AAA" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1974" box="[1048,1198,1412,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dolioponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFBA8FA6FFB3A1AAA" box="[1048,1198,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Dolioponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 3); propodeal lobes usually present; jugal lobe usually present; petiolar tergum and sternum distinct; cinctus between abdominal pre- and posttergites IV usually present; and abdominal sternum IX unpronged and edentate. Three final sets of characters are required for identification: 1) (
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFC0BFA06FBC2193C" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1901" box="[955,1110,1517,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platythyreini">Platythyreini</taxonomicName>
) mandibles triangular, tibial spur formula 2,2; 2) (
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFE54F9FAFDDF1918" box="[484,587,1553,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ponerini">Ponerini</taxonomicName>
) mandibles spatulate, linear, or nub-like and mesonotum not anteriorly elongated; and 3) (
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFE76F9DFFDBA197A" box="[454,558,1588,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ponerini">Ponerini</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFD8CF9DFFD46197A" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1974" box="[572,722,1588,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dolioponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFD8CF9DFFD46197A" box="[572,722,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Dolioponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) forewing with three closed cells, propodeal lobes present, antennal toruli situated at anterior extreme of head, oblique mesopleural sulcus absent, and cinctus present. The eighth abdominal tergum of male 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFCA3F991FC1C19A0" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau" authorityYear="1835" box="[787,904,1658,1684]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponerinae">Ponerinae</taxonomicName>
may be spiniform, a unique state among the 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFF53F976FEF81983" box="[227,364,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Formicidae</taxonomicName>
, but this character is not present in all genera and may be interspecifically variable. The spur formula of 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFED7F92AFE5E19EF" box="[359,458,1729,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Ponerini">Ponerini</taxonomicName>
is variable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D6511FF86B14AFF53F8E9FBC41B36" lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B98369AFF86B14BFF53F8E9FEFE1828" blockId="46.[227,362,1794,1820]" box="[227,362,1794,1820]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<heading id="D0D081F6FF86B14BFF53F8E9FEFE1828" bold="true" box="[227,362,1794,1820]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFF53F8E9FEFE1828" bold="true" box="[227,362,1794,1820]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369AFF86B14BFF53F8DAFA0818EC" blockId="46.[227,1436,1841,2008]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFEA7F8DAFE18187F" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint-Fargeau" authorityYear="1835" box="[279,396,1841,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponerinae">Ponerinae</taxonomicName>
is global in distribution and has recently been provided a molecular phylogeny (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B6BFF86B14BFA88F8DAFE8B185A" author="Schmidt C." pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="201 - 250" refId="ref32607" refString="Schmidt C. 2013. Molecular phylogenetics of ponerine ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae: Ponerinae). Zootaxa 3647: 201 - 250. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3647.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Schmidt 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and a global generic revision (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B6BFF86B14BFD38F8BFFC2E185A" author="Schmidt C. A. &amp; Shattuck S. O." box="[648,954,1876,1902]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 242" refId="ref32646" refString="Schmidt C. A. &amp; Shattuck S. O. 2014. The higher classification of the ant subfamily Ponerinae (Hymenoptera: Formicidae), with a review of ponerine ecology and behavior. Zootaxa 3817: 1 - 242. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3817.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">Schmidt &amp; Shattuck 2014</bibRefCitation>
), which did not treat males; the subfamily is now comprised of 47 valid genera. Males are unknown for 9 genera (
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFB87F89CFB7118A5" authorityName="Santschi" authorityYear="1914" box="[1079,1253,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Asphinctopone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFB87F89CFB7118A5" box="[1079,1253,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Asphinctopone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFB45F893FA0118A6" authorityName="Schmidt &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2014" box="[1269,1429,1912,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Austroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFB45F893FA0118A6" box="[1269,1429,1912,1938]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Austroponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFF53F871FEFA1880" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="2006" box="[227,366,1946,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Boloponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFF53F871FEFA1880" box="[227,366,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Boloponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFECAF870FD911880" box="[378,517,1947,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Feroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFECAF870FD911880" box="[378,517,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Feroponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D19FF86B14BFDA2F871FD311880" authorityName="Schmidt &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2014" box="[530,677,1946,1972]" class="Hexapoda" family="Formicidae" genus="Fisheropone" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B953EA88FF86B14BFDA2F871FD311880" box="[530,677,1946,1972]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fisheropone</emphasis>
